Class C2SBenchmark

    • production.C2SBenchmark

  • class C2SBenchmark
extends java.lang.Object
    Class called by the JUnit testing framework when testing queries for correctness of output. Only testing frameworks should use this class.

      • queryTest

        boolean queryTest(java.lang.String originalCypherInput,
                  java.io.File f_cypher,
                  java.io.File f_sql,
                  java.lang.String dbName,
                  java.lang.String propsLocation)
        queryTest is the method that combines the translation of Cypher with the checking of the outputs.
        Parameters:
        originalCypherInput - The Cypher input to be converted.
        f_cypher - The file to store the results from Neo4j in to.
        f_sql - The file to store the results from Postgres/other relational backend in to.
        dbName - The name of the relational database to execute the SQL on.
        propsLocation - The file location of the c2s_props.properties file.
        Returns:
        True if the translation was successful, false otherwise.
